 :tx/rationale "DAEMON-W0: Fix BUG 2 — write_slim_cache fingerprint must reflect in-memory state, not disk state. PROBLEM: layout.rs:569 write_slim_cache() calls list_tx_hashes() at flush time, which lists ALL .edn files on disk — including ones written by other processes. The fingerprint says 'I represent files A,B,C,D' but store.bin only has datoms from A,B,C. Next reader: fingerprint match → cache hit → stale. SOLUTION: write_slim_cache() accepts known_hashes parameter from caller. LiveStore::flush() passes self.known_hashes. Fingerprint reflects exactly what the store contains. If the flush is stale, the fingerprint won't match the full disk state → next reader gets cache miss → rebuilds correctly. Staleness becomes one-command transient, not persistent. VERIFICATION: (1) Unit test: flush with partial known_hashes → next load detects mismatch → rebuilds with all hashes. (2) proptest: for any subset of hashes, fingerprint(subset) != fingerprint(full_set) when subset != full_set. FILES: layout.rs (write_slim_cache signature), live_store.rs (flush passes known_hashes). DEPENDS-ON: None (leaf task). BLOCKS: Wave 1 (defense-in-depth for direct-mode fallback)."
